{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e4018a7d-6e3a-48a4-ae84-81f6a585e1e0","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `.csproj`**\n```xml\n<!-- Change -->\n<TargetFramework>net10.0</TargetFramework>\n<!-- To -->\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`**\n```jsonc\n// Change SDK version to 11.0.100 (or latest 11.x patch)\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`**\n```dockerfile\n# Update base images\nmcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0\nmcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0\n```\n\n**Also check:**\n- Update any `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*` / `Microsoft.Extensions.*` NuGet packages to their 11.x versions.\n- Review the [.NET 11 breaking changes](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/11.0) for anything affecting your app.\n- Run `dotnet restore && dotnet build` to verify everything compiles.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"25babb2b-8e34-4063-82a7-6712f89f3046","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no codebase to explore. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":339,"requestId":"1426:33DFCD:15E14C6:196F692:69EC1BA5"},"id":"39e888dc-7879-4feb-8f0c-31b0ce2c468e","timestamp":"2026-04-25T01:41:00.113Z","parentId":"3b02a212-36f9-42c5-969c-e036bb1bfa4b"}
